        <h3 class="text-center" id="who-are-we">what is Youphonica</h3>
        <p>Youphonica is a site where musicians can upload video and audio of 
            previous concerts as well as livestream their concerts to their
            fans. The aim of Youphonica is to be a platform open to as many 
            musicians as possible and allow them to easily create an account
            and have another way to generate income from their music. Youphonica
            also aims to help and promote small/up and coming artists and 
            have the site focus on finding a way of bringing music to as
            many people as possible. 
        </p>

        <p class="text-center"> if you can't make it to the concert, 
            the concert will be brought to you!</p>

        <h3 class="text-center" id="how-to-create-artist-account">how do I create an artist account?</h3>
        <p>If you haven't already created an account on the site. You will need to do that by clicking
            here.

            If you have already created an account with the site, you should see a link to apply for 
            an artist account in the dropdown menu at the top of the page. Or you can click here.

            You will then be directed to a page where you will input information about yourself/your band.
            You will then be redirected to a page to verify your identity. This is done to help ensure
            that people aren't imporsonating artists and making money off of their music. To learn more about
            this please read our terms of service. After you complete the application form and verification
            process you should recieve an email to let you know that you have been verified with the next 
            few days or sooner depending on the volume of people trying to open accounts. if you haven't received
            an email within a week you have likely not been verified, if this is the case and 
            you believe that you should have been verified, please get into contact with us at: support@Youphonica.com
            
            Once you have been verified you will need to fill out payment details before you can create posts
            so that you can recieve payments. To find out more about payments please read our terms of service.
        </p>


        <h3 class="text-center" id="create-post">How do I schedule a livestream?</h3>
        <p>You can schedule a livestream by going to your artists page and clicking new post. 
            This will then send you to a page to choose between a livestream, video and audio. 
            Select schedule a livestream, fill out the form including selecting the time of the 
            show and the correct timezone. Then upload the thumbnail. once this is complete you 
            should see the livestream on your artists page under posts. If you want the post to 
            be public and people to be able to purchase it then make sure the visibility is set to public. 
            If you do not want other people to see
            it or purchase it, please make sure to set the visibility to private. When the event is near
            both you and the people who have purchased it will be notified. If people have pre-ordered 
            your livestream you cannot set it to private. If the post for the scheduled livestream is deleted
            before the livestream takes place or is not streamed to the people who paid for it at the time
            it was scheduled for, the customers may be entitled to a refund. To find out more
            about refunds please read our terms of service.
        </p>


        <h3 class="text-center" id="create-post">How do I post a video?</h3>
        <p>You can post a video by going to your artists page and clicking new post. 
            This will then send you to a page to choose between a livestream, video and audio. 
            Select the video, fill out the form and then wait for the video to upload and then
            upload the thumbnail. Once this is complete you should see the video on your artists
            page under posts. If you want the post to be public and people to be able to purchase it
            then make sure the visibility is set to public. If you do not want other people to see
            it or purchase it, please make sure to set the visibility to private.
        </p>



        <h3 class="text-center" id="create-post">How do I post audio?</h3>
        <p>You can post a video by going to your artists page and clicking new post. 
            This will then send you to a page to choose between a livestream, video and audio. 
            Select the Audio, fill out the form including selecting the audio files and inputing 
            the track name. Wait for the files to upload and then
            upload the thumbnail. Once this is complete you should see the post on your artists
            page under posts. If you want the post to be public and people to be able to purchase it
            then make sure the visibility is set to public. If you do not want other people to see
            it or purchase it, please make sure to set the visibility to private.
        </p>


        <h3 class="text-center" id="how-to-create-artist-account">what is the commission?</h3>
        <p>Youphonica tries to be fair and competitive in regards to commission. For sales of Video,
            Audio and pre-orders of Livestreams, The artist recieves 75% of the revenue with Youphonica taking
            a commission of 25%. in terms of donations to artists, Youphonica takes 10% commission on each donation with 90% going to the artist. 
            to find out more about commission, fees and payments please read our terms of service.
        </p>


        
